default&#xa0;defaultQ4. What scope, scale and remit should the defaultBBC have?default4.1 
default              
defaultThe BBC Trust’s introduction to the Director-General’s 2010 Strategy Review asked the Executive where the BBC’s focus and scale could be reduced “if necessary”. 
default4.2
default 
default              
defaultThe Executive response was contained in the section entitled ‘Doing fewer
default things better’
default which recommended prioritising some areas and recommending some 
defaultservice closures (some of whic
defaulth materialised, others did not, demonstrating the difficulty of cutting services which audiences value greatly). It may be that some services, fo
defaultr example Radio 2, can afford to become more focused and specialist at the risk of losing audience (as the Trust implied).
default4.3
default 
default              
defaultThe BBC is almost certainly larger than it needs to be, but this invites the question as to how large the BBC ‘needs to be’ to f
defaultulfil its mission. 
defaultWe would welcome a better balance between the content  areas: information, education and entertainment, both in terms of broadcast hours and of funding (see 5.3 below). 
default&#xa0;
defaultQ5 Should the BBC’s output and services be provided to any greaterdefault or lesser degree for particular audiences?default5.1 
default              
defaultIt appears to be accepted that the BBC should devote the
default largest
