default5.3
default              
defaultWe think that ‘fair’ and ‘a
defaultppropriate’, having regard to what are considered core elements of public service broadcasting, are preferable to ‘proportionate’. In terms of television spend, 61% for BBC One, 22%  for BBC Two and 2.7% for BBC Four does not seem ‘fair’, ‘appropriate’ or 
defaulteven ‘proportionate’ for a public service broadcaster. BBC radio 
defaultfunding is
default similar
defaultly discrepant
default, the service
default 
defaultlicence spend of Radio 3 (
defaultthe only one of the five network stations to have
default no digital only ‘sister’ station) being the lowest of the BBC network 
defaultstations
default, to cover what is arguably the most varied and expensive remit in terms of specialist musics and speech/arts programmes
default.
default5.4
default              
defaultWe object to the crude 
defaultdemographic
default argument that ‘older listeners’ are overserved or at least adequately served. 
defaultWe totall
defaulty support special children’s services, but in terms of separate, differentiated services, younger audiences (children and young adults) are, by comparison, well served in terms of both services and funding (CBeebies, CBBC, BBC Three, Radio 1, Radio 1Xtra, 
defaultplus to an extent, the Asian Network and 6 Music). Adult audiences are overwhelmingly treated as ‘general audiences’ and anything ‘new’ or ‘serious’ is treated at an intellectually elementary (‘accessible’) level e.g. Radio 3 is more concerned to introduce
default new listeners to classical music than to cater for its existing music audience.
