defaultQ7. How have the BBC’s commercial activities during the current Charter fitted with the BBC’s public purposes and have they achieved an adequate return for defaultlicence fee payers? What should be the aims, scope and scale of such activities beyond 2016?default7.1
default              
defaultIt seems right that programmes which have been paid for by the licence fee payer should be marketed commercially in such a way as to provide a return which can
default be reinvested to fund further programming.
