defaultQ12default              defaultHow should the BBC be governed, regulated and held accountable beyond 2016?default12.1
default              
defaultThe last government’s new model for the governance of the BBC  has been in operation for less than seven years. The Charter put in place 
defaulta new framework by which the BBC, especially the BBC Executive, could be held to account in the interests of the licence fee payer, the BBC Trust being the sovereign body charged with protecting the interests of the public.
default12.2
default              
defaultOur own experience relates 
defaultmost closely to the way in which the new system of service licences and reviews (remits, content and editorial direction of the individual services) has been overseen by the Trust. 
default12.3
default              
defaultThe Trust issues the service licences; approves update
defaults, carries out 
defaultservice reviews and
default public consultations
default,
default and approves management strategies. 
defaultAt present the Trust seems both too remote to have sufficient knowledge and competence, and therefore too reliant on information from
default managers
default. That is a flaw of both the system 
defaultand the individuals.
default12.4
default              
defaultT
defaulthere is notionally an official procedure for complaining about a Trust action or decision, 
default but 
defaultin practice this consists of submitting the details to the Director of the Trust
default Unit for an oracular adjudication
default 
defaultwith
default no 
defaulttransparen
defaultt procedure. Lord Grade has
default urged the appointment of a BBC ombudsman, a measure which we 
defaultthink should be investigated.
